
apache
============

how check the apache that is intalled ?

	# httpd -v
	# php -v

how to install apache, php, mysql ?

	# yum -y install mysql mysql-server mysql-devel
	# yum -y install php php-mysql
	# yum -y install httpd

how to let it running when the server start automatically ? 

	# chkconfig httpd on
	# chkconfig mysqld on
	# /etc/init.d/httpd start
	# /etc/init.d/mysqld start

or

	# vi /etc/rc.d/rc.local
	  /etc/init.d/httpd start
	  /etc/init.d/mysqld start

how to set the vhost ?

open your httpd config file like

	# vi /etc/httpd/conf/http.conf

and, uncomment the next line

	NameVirtualHost *:80
	
	LoadModule Vhost_alias_modules/mod_vhost_alias.so

and open new file in `/etc/httpd/conf.d/vhost`, then wirte down look like the under code

	<VirtualHost *:80>
		ServerName	www.mypro.com
		DocumentRoot /var/www/html/mypro
		ErrorLog	/var/logs/mypro.error
		CustomLog	/var/logs/mypro.access common
	</VirtualHost>

	<VirtualHost *:80>
		ServerName	www.mypro2.com
		DocumentRoot /var/www/html/mypro2
		ErrorLog	/var/logs/mypro2.error
		CustomLog	/var/logs/mypro2.access common
	</VirtualHost>

